Armed Conflict in Colombia

Manuela Szinovatz

17/10/2018

For the analysis we are using data from the Colombian governmental organisation Unidad Victimas, that is in charge of registering all the victims of Columbias armed conflict. They can be downloaded here: https://cifras.unidadvictimas.gov.co/ Up until October 2018 a total number of 8.760.290 victims have been registered.

Violent Incidents

The following graphic shows the overall number of incidents in Colombias worst affected municipalities Incidents in this case reach from homicides, threats, torture, terroristic attacks and other kinds of violence. The grand majority of the displayed incidents hoewever are forced displacements.

Buenaventura has more than 40 percent more violent incidents than in the second-most affected municipality Medelln, although Medellin is 6.5 times bigger than Buenaventura in terms of population.

The following graph shows how the violent incidents in Buenaventura and Medelln have development over the last 23 years of conflict.
